{"parentUuid":"e7890dd9-cc1e-4ea5-be84-ee68281fbe33","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"skill_listing","content":"- ask-stakeholder: Fork or resume a saved \"stakeholder\" session to ask it questions — use to consult a converged plan or persona, or to poll a panel of stakeholders for reactions to a proposal.\n- detached-git-init: Initialise a git repo whose git dir lives outside the working tree, under ~/.git-detached/<project>. Use when a project must not contain a .git folder (e.g. iCloud/Obsidian synced dirs).\n- reviewables: How to write a reviewable post that distills plans, changesets and proposals for easy consumption by the user.\n- vendored-repos: Read-only store of vendored external library source at ~/Repos/vendors — consult it for idiomatic examples, real API usage, and internals before falling back to web search or guessing. Also covers adding a repo to the store.\n- vite-plus: When using vite+ (vite plus, vp), use this skill to understand the recommend best practices.\n- writing-style: Write in Daniel's voice. Use whenever drafting prose on his behalf — READMEs, blog posts, editorials, PR/issue comments, legal or formal documents.\n- create-stakeholder: Save THIS session as a \"stakeholder session\", and adopt the stakeholder role\n- stakeholders: List the stakeholder sessions saved for the current project","skillCount":8,"isInitial":true,"names":["ask-stakeholder","detached-git-init","reviewables","vendored-repos","vite-plus","writing-style","create-stakeholder","stakeholders"]},"type":"attachment","uuid":"7790bcab-d68e-4e1e-b35f-de29ff30d8d7","timestamp":"2026-07-17T21:18:17.506Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/private/var/folders/t8/bhx1lqx977df536xx99b4f480000gp/T/mdz-agentic-aeDR90","sessionId":"fe2a028e-d5f1-4655-94b2-b8fabf047836","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
